<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.289124>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A – F, Parvodeceptor infrequens female; A, habitus, dorsal; B, head and anterior prothorax, right lateral; C, thoracic sterna, ventral; D, pterpothoracic pleurae, right lateral; E, right fore wing, dorsal; F, posterior abdomen, ventral and tergum 9, dorsal. Abbreviations: A, antennomere; ac, anteclypeus; b, bucculae; ely, elytral forwing; f, frons; fp, frontal protuberances; g, gena; L labial segment; mse mesepisternum; mss, mesosternum; mte, metepisternum; mts, metasternum; ps, prosternum; S abdominal sterna; T 9, tergum 9; I, fore coxal cavity; II, midcoxal cavity; III, hind coxal cavity. All scale lines 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/289124/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

